> these two sites are on two servers and servers both in US but data no synchronized.

@kai0 https://0net.io is actually located in Panama

> 502 is happening on https://0net.io now.

@60 server was blowing up, not sure why, had to completely rebuid it, so we'll see what happens; but might be time for another upgrade if its a resource issue with our host. fyi, we have a devops (code staging) server at https://0net.xyz if you ever experience a problem at the main proxy.

> The proxy owner could increase the limit by changing the connection limit with the --global_connected_limit setting (by default its 512)

The problem we often have with https://0net.io is RAM spikes (i believe from serving content, not necessarily the number of zites). We are planning an upgrade in about a month or so, but might need to move up that timetable if the downtime becomes a bigger issue (see here https://status.0net.io/). Our alternative is a new custom client that is optimized for serving thousands of zites (still in dev http://127.0.0.1:43110/supeer.bit).

> I still think the best way is we visit server our client can synchronize data with the client which is running on the server.

@kai0 are you familiar with [DHT](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Distributed_hash_table)? in ethereum, its very easy for clients to stay in sync, because everyone queries the same state of the "ethereum virtual machine (evm)". dht offers something ["similar"](https://libtorrent.org/dht_store.html), but unlike blockchain, its FREE! this problem could potentially be solved once [DHT is implemented](https://zeronet.io/docs/help_zeronet/donate/#dht-support) into the zeronet client.

---

> i'm also considering upgrade my server these days because zeronet eats up too much ram and always crashes and causes a 502

@60 we aren't very confident in the stability of the current proxy, since the client seems to be optimized for "normal" users and not for large-scale hosting (based on what I've seen from the debug logs). we're working on a node/js-based client & server that WILL be optimized for such use (taking advantage of v8's event loop and other enhancments). should be ready soonish'
